Definition A.4.2: Categorical-Level Representation:

Concept: This definition attempts to capture all possible category assignments in a single set C:sub:Î¶. Each element x of C:sub:Î¶ represents one possible categorical interpretation, and it's a set of ordered pairs mapping word indices to categories.

Formula: x âˆˆ C:sub:Î¶ â†” x = { (i, C:sub:L(m)) | âˆƒ i âˆˆ N:sub:Î›(Î¶): (Î¶{i} âˆˆ C:sub:L(m)) }

